  "response": "Here are some recommended books for GATE CSE 2018 and DRDO 2018 preparation:\n\nGATE CSE Preparation:\n\n1. Theory of Computation\n- \"Introduction to Automata Theory, Languages, and Computation\" by Hopcroft\n- \"Theory of Computation\" by Michael Sipser\n\n2. Data Structures and Algorithms\n- \"Data Structures and Algorithms\" by Cormen\n- \"Data Structures in C\" by Lipschutz\n\n3. Computer Networks\n- \"Computer Networks\" by Tanenbaum\n- \"Data Communications and Networking\" by Forouzan\n\n4. Operating Systems\n- \"Operating System Concepts\" by Silberschatz\n- \"Modern Operating Systems\" by Tanenbaum\n\n5. Database Management Systems\n- \"Database System Concepts\" by Korth\n- \"Introduction to Database Systems\" by C.J. Date\n\n6. Computer Architecture\n- \"Computer Organization and Design\" by Patterson and Hennessy\n- \"Computer Architecture\" by Hennessy\n\n7. Programming and Aptitude\n- \"GATE Guide for Computer Science\" by GK Publication\n- \"GATE Computer Science and Information Technology\" by Tata McGraw Hill\n\nDRDO Preparation:\n- Previous year question papers\n- General Science books\n- Current affairs magazines\n- Mathematics and Reasoning books\n\nRemember to complement book study with online resources and mock tests.",
